Recommends: python3
Description: NSA software reverse engineering framework
 Ghidra is a free and open-source software reverse engineering (SRE) framework
 developed by the National Security Agency (NSA) Research Directorate. It
 supports analysis of compiled code on a variety of platforms including Windows,
 macOS, and Linux.
 .
 Features include disassembly, assembly, decompilation, graphing, and scripting,
 along with hundreds of built-in analysers for ELF, PE, Mach-O, raw binaries,
 and cartridge formats. A plugin API enables custom analysers written in Java or
 Python (via Jython/PyGhidra).
 .
 This package ships the pre-built official Linux release from upstream. The
 native decompiler (support/decompile) is a pre-compiled x86_64 ELF binary.
 Run with the ghidra command or ghidra-headless for batch (non-GUI) analysis.
